snippet.textDisplay:
*Ryzen 4000 reason for 500 series motherboards...*
Speculation only, but I'm fairly certain the motherboard CHIPSET is designed to work more with the newer CPU's to obtain optimal performance. That includes optimal voltage regulation. I have no doubt they COULD make the CPU's work in 400 and 300 series boards easily but NOT at full performance which would confuse the message... it's not a complete guess as they talked about getting 200MHz boost vs previous boards with the X570 boards on the 300 series CPU's if things were optimal; that didn't really materialize but it does seem like there is some sort of critical hardware there to work with the VRM's and get optimal performance.
